    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Nader's Wrong on Gore</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Carol Greitzer letter on Oct 26 article scores Ralph Nader's attacks on Vice Pres Al Gore</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Under Fire From Democrats, Nader Assails Gore's Record'' (news article, Oct. 26):</p>
        <p>Rather than castigate Al Gore for ''promises broken'' on the environment, Ralph Nader and his followers should marvel that there were so many progressive accomplishments in the Clinton-Gore administration -- despite the machinations of a very hostile Congress.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Under Fire From Democrats, Nader Assails Gore's Record'' (news article, Oct. 26):</p>
        <p>Rather than castigate Al Gore for ''promises broken'' on the environment, Ralph Nader and his followers should marvel that there were so many progressive accomplishments in the Clinton-Gore administration -- despite the machinations of a very hostile Congress.</p>
        <p>If Mr. Nader is sincerely interested in issues, he should end his destructive campaign and channel his talents into electing a Democratic House and Senate that would do a better job of enacting a liberal Democratic agenda.</p>
        <p>CAROL GREITZER  New York, Oct. 26, 2000</p>
        <p>The writer was a member of the New York City Council, 1969-91.</p>
      </block>
